I can help you with that! In Go, to do something is quite similar to in C or other languages, but with added benefits such as strong typing and efficient memory management. 

Here's a basic example of how to print "Hello World" using the `fmt` package in Go:

```go
package main

import (
    "fmt"
)

func main() {
    fmt.Println("Hello, world!")
}
```

You can find the source code and documentation for other functions [here](http://golang.org/pkg/). To learn more about Go itself, you may want to look at the following resources:

- [Go Tutorial](http://www.go-tutorials.com/)
- [Learn Go Programming](https://golang.org/doc/learn)
